      "title": "Use the root product",
      "content": "For a quadratic $ax^2+bx+c=0$, the product of the solutions is $c/a$.",
      "formula": "$$\\text{product of roots} = \\frac{c}{a}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Substitute the coefficients",
      "content": "Here, $a=1$ and $c=-80$.<br/>$$c/a=-80/1=-80$$<br/>The answer is <strong>A</strong>."
    }
  ]
